hopobject.body: Directory enquiries apollo energy gumshoe Coughlin is an offensive coach, but not considered an offensive genius. He has guided the Giants on two unexpectedly amazing playoffs runs that led to Super Bowl titles, but several second-half collapses at least raise the issue of whether he reaches his players all the time. He doesn't have the personality or commanding presence of Parcells although becoming more player-friendly in 2007 saved his coaching career. He might need one more run deep into the playoffs â not necessarily another championship â to convince the 44 voters that he qualifies for the HOF. He is borderline right now.
